        <body>
            <div type="edition" subtype="primary" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="la" resp="#JP" source="#autopsy">
                    <ab>
                         <lb n="1"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><orig>N</orig><gap reason="illegible" unit="character" quantity="1"/><gap reason="lost" unit="character" extent="unknown"/>
                    </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus" resp="#JP">
                <listApp>
                    <app><note>Text based on autopsy</note></app>
                    <app loc="1"><note>A vertical is preserved after the N, with extended foot serif, joining that of the N; I is most likely.</note></app>
                    </listApp> 
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#JP">
                <p/>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary" resp="#JP">
                <p>The fragment is unpublished. The size suggests a public commemorative text of some description, honorific or building related, in an area which seems to have been a mixture of public and domestic contexts in the Imperial period.</p>
            </div>
